CSS Day 4: Display Property

The display property controls how an element appears on the page.

This is a very important topic before learning Flexbox.

1. Block Elements

Block elements:

✅ Start on a new line
✅ Take full available width

Examples:

<div>Div</div>
<p>Paragraph</p>
<h1>Heading</h1>

Example:

<div>Java</div>
<div>React</div>

Output:

Java
React

Each element starts on a new line.

2. Inline Elements

Inline elements:

✅ Stay on the same line
❌ Width and height usually don't work as expected

Examples:

<span>Java</span>
<span>React</span>

Output:

Java React

Other inline elements:

<span>
<a>
<strong>
<em>
3. Inline-Block

Combination of block and inline.

✅ Stays on same line
✅ Width and height work

Example:

<div class="box">Java</div>
<div class="box">React</div>
.box {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 150px;
    height: 80px;
    border: 1px solid black;
}

Output:

[ Java ] [ React ]
4. Display None

Hides an element completely.

.hide {
    display: none;
}
<p class="hide">Hidden Text</p>

Output:

Nothing is shown.

